<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">Themes and topics<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">We invite submissions of r=
esearch papers on the foundational theory of analogies, on interactions bet=
ween case-based reasoning and analogies, as well
 as on applicative use-case studies.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">Topics of interest include=
, but are not limited to:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">* Foundational theory of a=
nalogies:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Axiomatic =
approaches to analogical proportions;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogy-pr=
eserving functions;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Interactio=
ns between case-based and analogical reasoning.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">* Applications:<o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogical=
 reasoning in machine learning;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogical=
 reasoning in visual domains;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogical=
 reasoning in Natural Language Processing;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogical=
 reasoning in healthcare;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogy ba=
sed explanations;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogies =
in software engineering;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp; &nbsp; - Analogies =
in knowledge management.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">Submission Guidelines<o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">Submitted papers must be f=
ormatted according to Springer LNCS formatting guidelines, see:<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ar=
ial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black"><a href=3D"https://iccbr2022.loria.fr/cal=
l-for-papers/"><span lang=3D"EN-US">https://iccbr2022.loria.fr/call-for-pap=
ers/</span></a></span><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">We welcome contributions i=
n the form of extended abstracts (up to two pages &#43; 1 page for referenc=
es) and long papers (up to six pages &#43; 1 page for references).<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">Submissions can describe e=
ither work in progress or mature work.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></=
p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">All papers will be&nbsp; t=
horoughly reviewed (single-blind).&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:black">Overlength and/or out-of-s=
cope papers will be rejected without review.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:12.0pt;font-=
